narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Only take if you're prepared for a seminar that is very unstructured. A lot of days it seemed like she didn't have anything actually prepared, but rather just went off of whatever tangents we produced. That said, it's a fairly easy class and not unenjoyable. Feels like it's taught by a TA though.

This class had a rather heavy workload but comprehensively covered many different aspects of sexuality, race, and religion. I would definitely recommend this class to another student, as long as they are willing to do the amount of work and are truly interested in the subject matter.
